{"word":"G4267 - προγινώσκω - proginṓskō - prog-in-oce'-ko - Foreknow","slug":"G4267","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">προγινώσκω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>proginṓskō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>prog-in-oce'-ko"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Foreknow"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>προγινώσκω</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Proginosko</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>prog-in-oce'-ko</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> to have knowledge before hand </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> to foreknow </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> of those whom God elected to salvation </p> <p class='li260'><b>3.</b> to predestinate </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G4253\">G4253</a> and <a href=\"#/G1097\">G1097</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 12:55,1 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Verb <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G4253\">G4253</a> and <a href=\"#/G1097\">G1097</a>; to <i>know beforehand</i> that is <b><i>foresee</i></b>: - foreknow (ordain) know (before). "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1097\">G1097</a>, <a href=\"#/G1106\">G1106</a>, <a href=\"#/G1107\">G1107</a>, <a href=\"#/G1108\">G1108</a>, <a href=\"#/G1110\">G1110</a>, <a href=\"#/G176\">G176</a>, <a href=\"#/G1921\">G1921</a>, <a href=\"#/G1922\">G1922</a>, <a href=\"#/G2607\">G2607</a>, <a href=\"#/G4268\">G4268</a>, <a href=\"#/G4774\">G4774</a>"}]}